                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> ARLINGHAM. <persName>King Henry II</persName> grants in frankalmoigne to the 
                  church of <placeName key="place_1083541">St. Leonard of Stanley</placeName>, the church of 
                  <placeName key="place_1083388">Erlingham</placeName> with all the tithes of the same village, and one
                  virgate of land at <placeName key="place_1083475">Maismore</placeName> which
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> de <surname>Berchelaio</surname>
                        </persName> gave
                  to the said church in frankalmoigne. Besides he granted to the same church 60s. 
                  per annum, namely, <persName>
                           <forename>Hardacr</forename>' de <surname>Berchelaio</surname>
                        </persName>,
                  which the same Roger gave them of his rents, as the charter of Henry his 
                  grandfather witnesseth. At <placeName role="date" key="place_1083374">Dover</placeName>, in transitu regis. 
                  (<origDate when="1158" precision="low">c. 1158</origDate>.)
                   </p>
                  </msItem>
